reviews.text: This place really surprised me after only a 3.8 rating. The sauce was good, plenty of toppings, and my family really enjoyed the crust too. We did just their pepperoni and cheese for a kids party but we can't wait to try more flavors. 6 pizzas done in about 25 minutes and they are good sized too.  Will visit again!

By far the best loaded Hawaiian pizza I‚Äôve had anywhere!! I drive 1.5hrs one way just to get it at least once during my work rotations

Also they have an amazing teenage mutant ninja turtles picture on the wall so obviously they have great style.

Ordered delivery as I was staying at the Roosevelt. Coming from CT and being a pizza snob (IYKYK) I didn't know what to expect. Ordered a jalapeno pineapple as my usual go to, not a fan of the crust but the pizza was nicely topped. (Once I added red pepper and Parmesan.) The lady delivery driver was very nice. Tried their jalapeno popper pizza yesterday and that was also good. Still meh on the crust but it was cooked well and quite tasty.

As I ordered delivery I can't say how the actual place is but will give it a try sometime!

detailedReviews.author: Jared Murray
detailedReviews.text:
I was pretty stoked when the motherload pizza showed up 26 minutes after I ordered it.  I was hungry and enjoy grabbing local pie when I get an opportunity in my travels.  The pizza looked good.  It was hot. Definitely didn't have the "double cheese" i had asked for but I wasn't going to be picky.... Though that might have helped with keeping the toppings on... pizza shrapnel and lack of cheese aside... the crust on the bottom was soggy and undercooked.  The crust was tasty,  though... even if it wasn't completely sliced through...  Unfortunately,  as they didn't use a box liner, so that paired with the soggy underside that became glue by morning,  made 2/3 of the pizza very difficult to eat.

That said.  All the elements of a fantastic pizza were there... seemed to be quality ingredients and it tasted good.

I'll give them another chance next time I'm through this part of ND and toss an update on here.
